You are working on Lucas AI Hub, a React 19 + Vite 8 + Tailwind CSS 4 web app for browsing and managing AI agent templates. Read CLAUDE.md for full documentation.

## Critical Rules

- JavaScript only (.jsx), no TypeScript
- Functional components with hooks, no class components
- Default exports only: `export default function ComponentName() {}`
- All icons from `lucide-react` — no other icon libraries
- Tailwind utility classes only — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- react-router 7 for routing — use `<Link>`, `useParams`, `useNavigate`
- No external state management — use useState + Context API only

## File Organization

- Components go in `src/components/` (flat, no subdirectories)
- Context providers go in `src/context/`
- Static data goes in `src/data/` (JSON for structured data, JS for content)
- Routes are defined in `src/App.jsx`

## Styling Rules

- Theme uses CSS variables via `data-theme` attribute (dark/light)
- Custom theme colors are mapped in `src/index.css` under `@theme`
- Use semantic Tailwind classes: `bg-bg-primary`, `text-text-secondary`, `border-border-subtle`
- Dynamic colors use a `colorMap` object: `{ bg, border, icon, tag, glow }` per color
- Available colors: blue, green, purple, amber, rose, cyan
- For hover on dark bg use `hover:bg-white/5`, light mode overrides are handled in CSS

## Data Patterns

- Agent IDs are kebab-case: `"frontend-developer"`
- Agent icons must be valid lucide-react exports: `"Monitor"`, `"Brain"`
- Agent categories: `"Development Team"` or `"AI Specialists"`
- Agent colors: `"blue" | "green" | "purple" | "amber" | "rose" | "cyan"`
- Teams reference agents by ID in an `agents` array

## Component Conventions

- Props are destructured in function parameters
- Use `variant` prop for components with multiple layouts (e.g., HeroSection, SearchFilterBar)
- Use `useMemo` for filtered/sorted lists
- Use `useStack()` hook for agent stack operations
- Use `useTheme()` hook for theme toggling
- Event handlers: `handleX` naming for complex handlers, inline arrows for simple ones
- Import icons with `import * as Icons from 'lucide-react'` when resolving dynamically

## When Adding Features

1. New agents → update `agents.json` + `agentContent.js`
2. New teams → update `teams.json` with valid agent IDs
3. New routes → add to Routes in `App.jsx`, add sidebar entry if top-level
4. New global state → create Context in `src/context/`, provide in `main.jsx`
5. New components → one file per component in `src/components/`
